## Configurations (multi-configuration IP)

One YAML per configuration lives in `cfg/` (`config_name` + `params:`;
`extends: <base.yaml>` deep-merges a base spec, the child file winning).
Select at run time:

```bash
make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test CFG=../cfg/<config>.yaml
```

Params become `+define+`/`-defparam` xrun flags and `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` fields
(via `+PARAM_<name>=` plusargs). Every simulation prints the config signature
banner (`config_name`, all param values, FNV-1a hash) and appends a record to
`verif_matrix.yaml`. Regressions: one `sim/{{ ip }}_<config_name>.vsif` per
configuration (session `{{ ip }}_<config_name>`), launched with
`make regress CFG=...`. Re-run `uvm_gen.py` with another configuration YAML to
create its vsif + cfg copy (nothing else changes).

## Dropping this env into an SoC environment

The env is self-contained (`{{ ip }}_`-prefixed packages, no tb_top or
hierarchical references). The SoC env builds ONE `{{ ip }}_env_cfg`, publishes
it via `uvm_config_db`, and flips the agents passive — the RTL then drives the
buses while monitors, scoreboard and coverage stay live:

```systemverilog
import {{ ip }}_env_pkg::*;

class soc_env extends uvm_env;
  {{ ip }}_env     {{ ip }}0_env;
  {{ ip }}_env_cfg {{ ip }}0_cfg;

  virtual function void build_phase(uvm_phase phase);
    super.build_phase(phase);
    {{ ip }}0_cfg = {{ ip }}_env_cfg::type_id::create("{{ ip }}0_cfg");
    {{ ip }}0_cfg.set_all_passive();       // RTL drives; monitors/coverage stay live
    {{ ip }}0_cfg.ral_env_owns_bus = 0;    // SoC owns the register bus
{% for a in agents %}
    {{ ip }}0_cfg.{{ a.name }}_cfg.vif = ...;  // from the SoC testbench
{% endfor %}
    // Register model: build the SoC model containing {{ ip }}_reg_block as a
    // child (add_submap(<ip base address>)), then: {{ ip }}0_cfg.regmodel = <child>;
    uvm_config_db #({{ ip }}_env_cfg)::set(this, "{{ ip }}0_env", "cfg", {{ ip }}0_cfg);
    {{ ip }}0_env = {{ ip }}_env::type_id::create("{{ ip }}0_env", this);
  endfunction
endclass
```

Compile collateral: reuse `sim/tb.f` minus its final `tb_top` line (see the
comment in the file). Prove passive readiness at IP level any time with
`make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test PASSIVE=1`.
